<subSubSection id="B9B6650D9705E36DF1A4FEF504CF0446" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F11336869705E36DF1A4FEF505A30575" blockId="6.[151,1436,258,877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF1A4FEF5070F06AD" bold="true" box="[199,321,366,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF382FEF4051F06AC" box="[737,849,367,390]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF382FEF4051F06AC" box="[737,849,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF2F7FEF405BC06AC" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[916,1010,366,390]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2F7FEF405BC06AC" box="[916,1010,366,390]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Differences in genitalia that allow recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF05FFE08078E0681" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[316,448,403,427]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF05FFE08078E0681" box="[316,448,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF0A4FE09046F0681" box="[455,545,402,427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0A4FE09046F0681" bold="true" box="[455,545,402,427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
when compared to 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF39CFE0805190681" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[767,855,403,427]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF39CFE0805190681" box="[767,855,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are: cornuti decreasing dramatically in size distally in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF1D7FE2C074206E4" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[180,268,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF1D7FE2C074206E4" box="[180,268,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and only slightly in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF363FE2C04CB06E4" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[512,645,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF363FE2C04CB06E4" box="[512,645,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Saccus more developed and markedly more produced in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF47BFE2C03D206E4" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[1304,1436,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF47BFE2C03D206E4" box="[1304,1436,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF1F4FE4106BC06D9" box="[151,242,474,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF1F4FE4106BC06D9" bold="true" box="[151,242,474,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Valvae with three lobes in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF345FE40043306D9" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[550,637,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF345FE40043306D9" box="[550,637,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but only two in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF25CFE40058D06D9" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[831,963,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF25CFE40058D06D9" box="[831,963,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF2A9FE41026A06D9" box="[970,1060,474,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2A9FE41026A06D9" bold="true" box="[970,1060,474,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF548FE4002AF06D9" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[1067,1249,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF548FE4002AF06D9" box="[1067,1249,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Episcepsis aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the cucullus shorter than valvula, while the opposite happens in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF3BDFE64052C053C" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[734,866,510,534]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF3BDFE64052C053C" box="[734,866,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF20AFE65058A053D" box="[873,964,510,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF20AFE65058A053D" bold="true" box="[873,964,510,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
In female genitalia, both species differ in the following characters: corpus bursae not as twisted or corrugated in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF2C8FDB802630511" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[939,1069,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2C8FDB802630511" box="[939,1069,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF550FDB902C20511" box="[1075,1164,546,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF550FDB902C20511" bold="true" box="[1075,1164,546,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
as in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF5AFFDB8036D0511" authorityName="Schaus" authorityYear="1889" box="[1228,1315,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aelia">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF5AFFDB8036D0511" box="[1228,1315,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. aelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter species lacks signa, while there are few ventral signa in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF269FDDC05C30574" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[778,909,582,606]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF269FDDC05C30574" box="[778,909,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF2F7FDDD05A30575" box="[916,1005,582,607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2F7FDDD05A30575" bold="true" box="[916,1005,582,607]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F11336869705E36DF1A4FDF104CF0446" blockId="6.[151,1436,258,877]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
When compared to 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF0C1FDF0044205A8" box="[418,524,619,642]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0C1FDF0044205A8" box="[418,524,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species differ in the following aspects: caecum slightly curved upwards in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF4E7FDF006AC058E" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF4E7FDF006AC058E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and straight in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF0FAFD160453058E" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[409,541,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0FAFD160453058E" box="[409,541,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF347FD170430058F" box="[548,638,652,677]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF347FD170430058F" bold="true" box="[548,638,652,677]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Saccus developed and with apex almost sharp in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF5D3FD16037D058E" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[1200,1331,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF5D3FD16037D058E" box="[1200,1331,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF458FD1703DB058F" box="[1339,1429,652,677]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF458FD1703DB058F" bold="true" box="[1339,1429,652,677]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and only weakly developed, with round apex and dorsally curved in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF2DBFD35026B05EF" box="[952,1061,686,709]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Heliura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2DBFD35026B05EF" box="[952,1061,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Tegumen densely covered with scales only in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF054FD5407F405CC" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[311,442,718,742]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF054FD5407F405CC" box="[311,442,718,742]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF0A2FD55045505CC" box="[449,539,718,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0A2FD55045A05CD" bold="true" box="[449,532,718,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF341FD5404A505CC" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[546,747,719,742]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF341FD5404A505CC" box="[546,747,719,742]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Episcepsis venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the cucullus shorter than valvula, while the opposite happens in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF074FD6A07D40422" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[279,410,752,776]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF074FD6A07D40422" box="[279,410,752,776]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF0C2FD7407B50422" box="[417,507,751,776]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0C2FD7407B50422" bold="true" box="[417,507,751,776]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
In female genitalia, we found the following differences: Dorsal surface of papillae anales with few setae in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF0D5FC89046D0403" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[438,547,786,809]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0D5FC89046D0403" box="[438,547,786,809]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and lacking setae in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF279FC8905EE0403" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[794,928,785,809]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF279FC8905EE0403" box="[794,928,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF2CAFC8A024B0400" box="[937,1029,785,810]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF2CAFC8A024B0400" bold="true" box="[937,1029,785,810]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Antevaginal lamella with posterior margin sinuous only in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF0C7FCA804410460" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[420,527,819,842]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF0C7FCA804410460" box="[420,527,819,842]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ductus seminalis arising from ductus bursae on the left side in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF58DFCA8033C0461" authority="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior, 2017" authorityName="Pinheiro &amp; Araujo Junior" authorityYear="2017" box="[1262,1394,819,843]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF58DFCA8033C0461" box="[1262,1394,819,843]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. atlantica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D8EB57EF9705E36DF419FCA906860447" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF419FCA906860447" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and from accessory bursa in 
<taxonomicName id="36AC4D059705E36DF373FCCE04340446" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1877" box="[528,634,853,876]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Episcepsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venata">
<emphasis id="C3D8EA949705E36DF373FCCE04340446" box="[528,634,853,876]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">E. venata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
